'''Cornelius Severin Scheel Schilbred''', often referred to as '''C. S. Schilbred''' (13 December 1906 – 10 April 1985) was a Norwegian genealogist, historian and educator. A school teacher and headmaster by occupation, he wrote extensively, and chaired the [[Norwegian Genealogical Society]] and the [[Norwegian Heraldry Society]].
==Early life== He was born in [[Eidanger]] as a son of [[Lieutenant Colonel]] Cornelius Mathias Schilbred (1878–1949) and Marie Henriette Petersen (1885–1965). In 1939 he married Margrethe Lomsdal (1908–2000).<ref name=nbl>{{cite encyclopedia|year=2004|title=C S Schilbred|encyclopedia=[[Norsk biografisk leksikon]]|first=Lars|last=Løberg|volume=8|editor=[[Knut Helle|Helle, Knut]]|publisher=Kunnskapsforlaget|location=Oslo|url=http://www.snl.no/.nbl_biografi/C_S_Schilbred/utdypning|language=Norwegian|accessdate=10 April 2009}}</ref>
Schilbred grew up in Eidanger and [[Oslo]]. He [[examen artium|finished]] his secondary education in 1925, enrolled in law studies and graduated with the [[cand.jur.]] degree in 1931. While studying he was an editor of the politically conservative periodical ''[[Minerva (Norwegian periodical)|Minerva]]'', and in 1928 a member of the board of the [[Norwegian Students' Society]]. In 1926, despite his young age, he was among the founders of the [[Norwegian Genealogical Society]].<ref name=nbl/> This was Norway's first national genealogical society.<ref name=about>{{cite news|url=http://www.genealogi.no/NSF/om_NSF.htm|title=Norsk Slektshistorisk Forening|publisher=Norwegian Genealogical Society|language=Norwegian|accessdate=10 April 2009|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070607043610/http://www.genealogi.no/NSF/om_NSF.htm|archivedate=7 June 2007|df=}}</ref>
==Later life== Schilbred spent his entire professional career as a teacher and headmaster in Oslo. In his spare time he had a considerable production of genealogical and local-historical works. He became a member of the board of the Norwegian Genealogical Society in 1952, served as vice chairman from 1957 and then chairman from 1968 to 1980. He edited its official periodical ''Norsk slektshistorisk tidsskrift'' from 1960 to 1967. He had formerly edited ''Tidsskrift for handelsutdannelse'' from 1948 to 1953, and also contributed to ''[[Aschehougs konversasjonsleksikon]]'' and ''[[Store norske leksikon]]''. He also co-founded the [[Norwegian Heraldry Society]] in 1969. He was a member of the board from the start, vice chairman from 1970 and then chairman from 1973 to 1974. He also served as vice chairman of the [[Norwegian Society for the Protection of Animals]].<ref name=nbl/>
Schilbred was decorated as a Knight, First Class of the [[Order of St. Olav]] in 1977. He was an honorary member of the Society for the Protection of Animals. He died in April 1985 in Oslo.<ref name=nbl/>
