[[File:Город гуннов (указатель).jpg|thumb|Entry to the Ivolga archaeo&shy;logical site. The Mongolian line of the road sign translates “[[Xiongnu]] city”.]]
The '''Ivolga archaeological site''' ([[Russian language|Russian]] Иволгинское городище ''Ivolginskoye gorodishche'') is the place of a fortified city of the [[Xiongnu]] which was founded in the 3rd century BC and destroyed in the 1st century BC.<ref>История Улан-Удэ ''(History of Ulan-Ude)'' [Ред. совет: Айдаев Г. А., Тучков С. М., Нагуслаева Т. М., Номогоева В. В., Матвеева А. И.]. – Кемерово: Кузбассвузидат, 2012. – p. 13–17</ref> It is sited near [[Ulan-Ude]], the capital of the [[Republic of Buryatia]], [[Russia]]. It is part of the [[folklore]] of this city where the Xiongnu are mixed up with the [[Huns]].<ref>{{cite web |publisher=Русское географическое общество (Russian Geographic Society) |title=Гуннский международный фонд ''(International Hun Fond)''|url=http://buryatia.rgo.ru/dela-i-proekty/gunnskij-mezhdunarodnyj-fond/ |date=2010 |access-date=November 22, 2013 |language=ru}}</ref>

