{{For|the general|Tracy A. Thompson}} {{Infobox writer |name = Tracy Price-Thompson |image = Tracy Price-Thompson (cropped).jpg |caption = |pseudonym = |birth_date = {{birth year and age|1963}} |birth_place = |death_date = |death_place = |occupation = [[Author]] |nationality = American |genre = |magnum_opus = }}
'''Tracy Price-Thompson''' (born 1963) is a speaker, novelist, and retired [[United States Army Corps of Engineers|United States Army Engineer]] officer. She is a veteran of the [[Gulf War]]. She self-published her first novel, ''Black Coffee'', at the age of 37. A story about an illicit romance between a female officer in the [[United States Army]] and a married enlisted man, it was quickly bought by Striver's Row, an imprint of [[Random House]]<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.accessmylibrary.com/coms2/summary_0286-8685825_ITM |title=Black Writers Appeal to a Growing Audience in Hackensack, N.J., Area. |newspaper=The Record |location=Hackensack, New Jersey |agency=Knight-Ridder/Tribune Business News |accessdate=April 3, 2008 |last=Johnson |first=Paul H. |date=February 3, 2002}}</ref> and became a bestseller.<ref name="USAToday2008">{{cite news |url=https://www.usatoday.com/life/books/reviews/2003-02-19-chick-lit_x.htm |title=New 'chick lit' spans humor, pathos |accessdate=April 3, 2008 |last=DiNardo |first=Kelly |date=February 19, 2003 |newspaper=USA Today}}</ref> She has since published five more novels: '' Chocolate Sangria'',<ref name="USAToday2008"/> ''A Woman's Worth'',<ref>{{cite news |url=https://query.nytimes.com/gst/fullpage.html?res=9D01EED7163EF930A35752C1A9639C8B63 |title=Arts, Briefly |first=Lawrence |last=Van Gelder |date=November 3, 2005 |newspaper=The New York Times}}</ref> ''Knockin' Boots'', ''Gather Together In My Name'' and ''1-900-ANYTIME''.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://aalbc.com/authors/tracyprice-thompson.htm |title=Tracy Price-Thompson |work=African American Literature Book Club}}</ref>
"A Woman's Worth" won the 2005 [[Hurston/Wright Legacy Award]] for Contemporary Fiction.<ref name="hwaward">{{cite web |url=http://www.hurstonwright.org/ProgramsAwards/legacyWinners2005.html |title=2005 Hurston/Wright LEGACY Award Winners |publisher=The Hurston/Wright Foundation |accessdate=November 10, 2012}}</ref>
